- He specializes in site reliability engineering (SRE), DevOps automation, cloud infrastructure, CI/CD pipelines, observability, and platform engineering.
- Sangharsh has deep expertise in modern cloud technologies, including Kubernetes, Docker, infrastructure as code, and automated delivery pipelines.
- He began his career as a software developer working with C++ and Python developer and later transitioned into DevOps and SRE, focusing on building reliable, scalable, and secure systems for modern SaaS platforms.
- Sangharsh actively contributes to the evolution of reliability engineering practices and is an advocate for integrating DevOps, SRE, security, and compliance into a unified operational framework for next-generation cloud platforms.
- He frequently writes and shares insights with the engineering community on topics such as SRE practices, automation, observability, and AI-driven operations.
- He is currently working as a senior site reliability engineer at Adobe, where he focuses on building scalable cloud infrastructure, modern CI/CD systems, and reliability platforms for large-scale SaaS products.   ❖ Parag Bhardwaj is a senior product manager and principal architect specializing in multi-cloud governance, FinOps, and AI-driven enterprise systems.

